1 raffle conducted pursuant to the Nebraska Lottery and Raffle Act may also
2 sell tickets or stubs for such raffles on its website and at events, and
3 such tickets or stubs may be purchased using a debit card online on the
4 website and at events in addition to other authorized methods of payment.
5 Sec. 7. Section 9-501, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
6 amended to read:
7 9-501 Sections 9-501 to 9-513 and section 10 of this act shall be
8 known and may be cited as the Nebraska Small Lottery and Raffle Act.
9 Sec. 8. Section 9-507, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
10 amended to read:
11 9-507 (1) Lottery shall mean a gambling scheme in which (a)
12 participants pay or agree to pay something of value for an opportunity to
13 win, (b) winning opportunities are represented by tickets differentiated
14 by sequential enumeration, (c) the winners are to be determined by a
15 random drawing of the tickets or by the method set forth in section
16 9-511.01 or section 10 of this act, and (d) the holders of the winning
17 tickets are to receive something of value.
18 (2) Except as provided in section 10 of this act, lottery Lottery
19 shall not include (a) any raffle, (b) any gambling scheme which uses any
20 mechanical, computer, electronic, or video gaming device which has the
21 capability of awarding something of value, free games redeemable for
22 something of value, or tickets or stubs redeemable for something of
23 value, (c) any activity authorized or regulated under the Nebraska Bingo
24 Act, the Nebraska County and City Lottery Act, the Nebraska Lottery and
25 Raffle Act, the Nebraska Pickle Card Lottery Act, the State Lottery Act,
26 section 9-701, or Chapter 2, article 12, or (d) any activity prohibited
27 under Chapter 28, article 11.
28 Sec. 9. Section 9-509, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
29 amended to read:
30 9-509 (1) Raffle shall mean a gambling scheme in which (a)
31 participants pay or agree to pay something of value for an opportunity to
-5-

