1 win, (b) winning opportunities are represented by tickets differentiated
2 by sequential enumeration, (c) winners are to be determined by a random
3 drawing of tickets or by the method set forth in section 9-511.01 or
4 section 10 of this act, and (d) at least eighty percent of all of the
5 prizes to be awarded are merchandise prizes which are not directly or
6 indirectly redeemable for cash by the qualifying nonprofit organization
7 conducting the raffle or any agent of the organization.
8 (2) Except as provided in section 10 of this act, raffle Raffle
9 shall not include (a) any gambling scheme which uses any mechanical,
10 computer, electronic, or video gaming device which has the capability of
11 awarding something of value, free games redeemable for something of
12 value, or tickets or stubs redeemable for something of value, (b) any
13 activity authorized or regulated under the Nebraska Bingo Act, the
14 Nebraska County and City Lottery Act, the Nebraska Lottery and Raffle
15 Act, the Nebraska Pickle Card Lottery Act, the State Lottery Act, section
16 9-701, or Chapter 2, article 12, or (c) any activity prohibited under
17 Chapter 28, article 11.
18 Sec. 10. (1) A qualifying nonprofit organization may conduct a
19 lottery or raffle that includes a progressive jackpot and multiple
20 drawing dates for a game such as, but not limited to, the Queen of
21 Hearts. In order to conduct a lottery or raffle in the method described
22 in this section, such organization shall (a) register each such lottery
23 or raffle game with the department and (b) post the rules for such
24 lottery or raffle in a visible location where such lottery or raffle is
25 conducted or where tickets for such lottery or raffle are sold.
26 (2) A qualifying nonprofit organization may sell a ticket for a
27 lottery or raffle conducted pursuant to this section through a vending or
28 dispensing device.
29 (3) The department may adopt and promulgate rules and regulations
30 for the conduct of a lottery or raffle utilizing the method authorized
31 pursuant to this section.
