1 Sec. 11. Section 9-511, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 9-511 Any qualifying nonprofit organization may conduct a lottery or
4 raffle that has gross proceeds not greater than fifteen thousand dollars.
5 Except as provided for a lottery or raffle conducted pursuant to section
6 10 of this act, each Each chance in such lottery or raffle shall have an
7 equal likelihood of being a winning chance. The gross proceeds shall be
8 used solely for charitable or community betterment purposes, awarding of
9 prizes, and expenses. Any qualifying nonprofit organization may conduct
10 one lottery per calendar month that has gross proceeds not greater than
11 fifteen thousand dollars. Any qualifying nonprofit organization may
12 conduct one or more raffles in a calendar month if the total gross
13 proceeds from such raffles do not exceed fifteen thousand dollars during
14 such month.
15 Sec. 12. Original sections 9-401, 9-411, 9-415, 9-431, 9-501,
16 9-507, and 9-509, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, and sections
17 9-427 and 9-511, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024, are
18 repealed.
